The paper deals with improving the uplink performance of cellular networks using decoupling of downlink and uplink association. This involves the use of multi-antenna base stations and single antenna user equipments, and the analysis is done using tools from stochastic geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of linear receivers and the derivation of tractable expressions, which suggests the categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of multi-antenna base stations and the analysis of beamforming gain suggest the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of load balancing, which suggests the category cs.COM (Computers and Society).
